+  'Dataset ds001_nsclc was analyzed with 50,000 records and outcome pfs_months. Effects below are signed differences or OLS coefficients in months unless otherwise stated; p-values are two-sided large-sample tests from the executed models.',
+  '',
+  'The strongest baseline prognostic findings were adverse disease burden and performance status. In the adjusted clinical model, stage_iv was associated with substantially shorter PFS (beta ' + betaLabel(t('stage_iv').beta) + ', p ' + pLabel(t('stage_iv').p) + '), as were has_brain_mets (beta ' + betaLabel(t('has_brain_mets').beta) + ', p ' + pLabel(t('has_brain_mets').p) + ') and each additional ECOG point (beta ' + betaLabel(t('ecog_ps').beta) + ', p ' + pLabel(t('ecog_ps').p) + '). Higher albumin was favorable (beta ' + betaLabel(t('albumin_g_dl').beta) + ' per g/dL, p ' + pLabel(t('albumin_g_dl').p) + '), while weight loss and LDH were unfavorable (weight loss beta ' + betaLabel(t('weight_loss_pct_6mo').beta) + ' per percentage point; LDH beta ' + betaLabel(t('ldh_per100').beta) + ' per 100 U/L; both highly significant).',
+  '',
+  'Demographic and disease-subtype effects were also present. Older age was positively associated with PFS (beta ' + betaLabel(t('age_years').beta) + ' per year, p ' + pLabel(t('age_years').p) + '), female sex was associated with lower PFS (beta ' + betaLabel(t('sex_female').beta) + ', p ' + pLabel(t('sex_female').p) + '), squamous histology was lower than adenocarcinoma (beta ' + betaLabel(t('histology_squamous').beta) + ', p ' + pLabel(t('histology_squamous').p) + '), and current smoking was lower than former smoking (beta ' + betaLabel(t('smoking_current').beta) + ', p ' + pLabel(t('smoking_current').p) + ').',
+  '',
+  'Several initially plausible adverse markers did not add independent signal once the major clinical factors were in the model. Liver metastases, bone metastases, and pleural effusion had coefficients near zero with p-values 0.569, 0.893, and 0.617, respectively. CRP and NLR were also null after adjustment (CRP beta ' + betaLabel(t('crp_mg_l').beta, 4) + ', p ' + pLabel(t('crp_mg_l').p) + '; NLR beta ' + betaLabel(t('nlr').beta, 4) + ', p ' + pLabel(t('nlr').p) + ').',
+  '',
+  'The dominant treatment-biomarker pattern was sotorasib in KRAS G12C disease. Before interaction modeling, kras_g12c had a large positive adjusted main association (beta ' + betaLabel(term(krasMainModel, 'kras_g12c').beta) + ', p ' + pLabel(term(krasMainModel, 'kras_g12c').p) + '). Explicit interaction testing showed that this was treatment-specific: treatment_sotorasib by kras_g12c was + ' + betaLabel(term(sotoKrasModel, 'sotorasib_x_kras').beta) + ' months (p ' + pLabel(term(sotoKrasModel, 'sotorasib_x_kras').p) + '). In subgroup means, sotorasib was associated with +2.552 months among KRAS G12C-positive patients but -0.005 months among KRAS G12C-negative patients.',
+  '',
+  'STK11 modified the sotorasib-KRAS pattern modestly but significantly. The treatment_sotorasib by kras_g12c by stk11_mutation coefficient was ' + betaLabel(term(sotoStk11Model, 'sotorasib_x_kras_x_stk11').beta) + ' months (p ' + pLabel(term(sotoStk11Model, 'sotorasib_x_kras_x_stk11').p) + '), indicating attenuation rather than reversal of the KRAS-positive sotorasib benefit.',
+  '',
+  'Other canonical treatment-biomarker hypotheses were not supported in this cohort. Pembrolizumab did not show stronger association with PFS at higher pdl1_tps (interaction beta ' + betaLabel(term(pembroPdl1Model, 'pembro_x_pdl1_per10').beta, 4) + ' per 0.10 PD-L1, p ' + pLabel(term(pembroPdl1Model, 'pembro_x_pdl1_per10').p) + ') or in tmb_high patients (interaction beta ' + betaLabel(term(pembroTmbModel, 'pembro_x_tmb_high').beta) + ', p ' + pLabel(term(pembroTmbModel, 'pembro_x_tmb_high').p) + '). EGFR- and ALK-driven subgroups did not show pembrolizumab resistance by interaction testing. Osimertinib by egfr_mutation was null (beta ' + betaLabel(term(osimEgfrModel, 'osimertinib_x_egfr').beta) + ', p ' + pLabel(term(osimEgfrModel, 'osimertinib_x_egfr').p) + '), and olaparib by brca2_mutation was null (beta ' + betaLabel(term(olapBrcaModel, 'olaparib_x_brca2').beta) + ', p ' + pLabel(term(olapBrcaModel, 'olaparib_x_brca2').p) + '), although brca2_mutation itself was associated with shorter PFS in that model (beta ' + betaLabel(term(olapBrcaModel, 'brca2_mutation').beta) + ', p ' + pLabel(term(olapBrcaModel, 'brca2_mutation').p) + ').',
+  '',
+  'Additional subgroup probes were largely negative. ALK fusion was not independently associated with shorter PFS after adjustment (beta ' + betaLabel(term(fusionModel, 'alk_fusion').beta) + ', p ' + pLabel(term(fusionModel, 'alk_fusion').p) + '). Autoimmune disease did not materially change the pembrolizumab association (interaction beta ' + betaLabel(term(autoimmuneModel, 'pembro_x_autoimmune').beta) + ', p ' + pLabel(term(autoimmuneModel, 'pembro_x_autoimmune').p) + '). Squamous histology did not modify sotorasib benefit after KRAS and STK11 terms were included (interaction beta ' + betaLabel(term(histologySotoModel, 'squamous_x_sotorasib').beta, 4) + ', p ' + pLabel(term(histologySotoModel, 'squamous_x_sotorasib').p) + ').',
+  '',
+  'The final combined model preserved the same conclusion: the sotorasib-KRAS interaction remained very large and positive (beta ' + betaLabel(term(finalModel, 'soto_x_kras').beta) + ', p ' + pLabel(term(finalModel, 'soto_x_kras').p) + '), STK11 attenuation remained significant (beta ' + betaLabel(term(finalModel, 'soto_x_kras_x_stk11').beta) + ', p ' + pLabel(term(finalModel, 'soto_x_kras_x_stk11').p) + '), and the pembrolizumab-PD-L1, pembrolizumab-TMB, osimertinib-EGFR, and olaparib-BRCA2 interaction terms remained small and non-significant.',
+].join('\n');
+
+fs.writeFileSync('transcript.json', JSON.stringify(transcript, null, 2) + '\n');
+fs.writeFileSync('analysis_summary.txt', summary + '\n');
+console.log('wrote transcript.json and analysis_summary.txt');
diff --git a/C:/Users/klkehl/are_llms_biased/data/ds001/tasks/nsclc/named/inspect_parquet.js b/C:/Users/klkehl/are_llms_biased/data/ds001/tasks/nsclc/named/inspect_parquet.js
new file mode 100644
index 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000..54776c9da8fce027ccb6578bc701e960a50d9680
--- /dev/null
+++ b/C:/Users/klkehl/are_llms_biased/data/ds001/tasks/nsclc/named/inspect_parquet.js
@@ -0,0 +1,313 @@
+const fs = require('fs');
+
+class CompactReader {
+  constructor(buf) {
+    this.buf = buf;
+    this.pos = 0;
+    this.lastField = [];
+  }
+  readByte() {
+    return this.buf[this.pos++];
+  }
+  readVarintBig() {
+    let shift = 0n;
+    let result = 0n;
+    while (true) {
+      const b = this.readByte();
+      result |= BigInt(b & 0x7f) << shift;
+      if ((b & 0x80) === 0) break;
+      shift += 7n;
+    }
+    return result;
+  }
+  readVarint() {
+    return Number(this.readVarintBig());
+  }
+  readZigZag() {
+    const n = this.readVarintBig();
+    const v = (n >> 1n) ^ (-(n & 1n));
+    return Number(v);
+  }
+  readI64() {
+    const n = this.readVarintBig();
+    return Number((n >> 1n) ^ (-(n & 1n)));
+  }
+  readDouble() {
+    const v = this.buf.readDoubleLE(this.pos);
+    this.pos += 8;
+    return v;
+  }
+  readBinary() {
+    const len = this.readVarint();
+    const out = this.buf.subarray(this.pos, this.pos + len);
+    this.pos += len;
+    return out;
+  }
+  readString() {
+    return this.readBinary().toString('utf8');
+  }
+  pushStruct() {
+    this.lastField.push(0);
+  }
+  popStruct() {
+    this.lastField.pop();
+  }
+  readFieldBegin() {
+    const b = this.readByte();
+    const type = b & 0x0f;
+    if (type === 0) return { type, id: 0 };
+    const delta = b >> 4;
+    let id;
+    if (delta === 0) id = this.readZigZag();
+    else id = this.lastField[this.lastField.length - 1] + delta;
+    this.lastField[this.lastField.length - 1] = id;
+    return { type, id };
+  }
+  readListBegin() {
+    const b = this.readByte();
+    let size = b >> 4;
+    const elemType = b & 0x0f;
+    if (size === 15) size = this.readVarint();
+    return { size, elemType };
+  }
+  skip(type) {
+    switch (type) {
+      case 0:
+        return;
+      case 1:
+      case 2:
+        return;
+      case 3:
+        this.pos += 1;
+        return;
+      case 4:
+      case 5:
+        this.readZigZag();
+        return;
+      case 6:
+        this.readI64();
+        return;
+      case 7:
+        this.pos += 8;
+        return;
+      case 8:
+        this.readBinary();
+        return;
+      case 9:
+      case 10: {
+        const { size, elemType } = this.readListBegin();
+        for (let i = 0; i < size; i++) this.skip(elemType);
+        return;
+      }
+      case 11: {
+        const size = this.readVarint();
+        if (size === 0) return;
+        const kt = this.readByte();
+        const vt = this.readByte();
+        for (let i = 0; i < size; i++) {
+          this.skip(kt);
+          this.skip(vt);
+        }
+        return;
+      }
+      case 12:
+        this.pushStruct();
+        while (true) {
+          const f = this.readFieldBegin();
+          if (f.type === 0) break;
+          this.skip(f.type);
+        }
+        this.popStruct();
+        return;
+      default:
+        throw new Error(`unknown compact type ${type} at ${this.pos}`);
+    }
+  }
+}
+
+function readStruct(reader, handlers) {
+  const out = {};
+  reader.pushStruct();
+  while (true) {
+    const f = reader.readFieldBegin();
+    if (f.type === 0) break;
+    const handler = handlers[f.id];
+    if (handler) out[handler.name] = handler.read(reader, f.type);
+    else reader.skip(f.type);
+  }
+  reader.popStruct();
+  return out;
+}
+
+const readI32 = r => r.readZigZag();
+const readI64 = r => r.readI64();
+const readString = r => r.readString();
+const readEnum = r => r.readZigZag();
+function readList(reader, elemReader) {
+  const { size } = reader.readListBegin();
+  const arr = [];
+  for (let i = 0; i < size; i++) arr.push(elemReader(reader));
+  return arr;
+}
+
+function readKeyValue(r) {
+  return readStruct(r, {
+    1: { name: 'key', read: readString },
+    2: { name: 'value', read: readString },
+  });
+}
+function readSchemaElement(r) {
+  return readStruct(r, {
+    1: { name: 'type', read: readEnum },
+    2: { name: 'type_length', read: readI32 },
+    3: { name: 'repetition_type', read: readEnum },
+    4: { name: 'name', read: readString },
+    5: { name: 'num_children', read: readI32 },
+    6: { name: 'converted_type', read: readEnum },
+    7: { name: 'scale', read: readI32 },
+    8: { name: 'precision', read: readI32 },
+    9: { name: 'field_id', read: readI32 },
+  });
+}
+function readStats(r) {
+  return readStruct(r, {
+    1: { name: 'max', read: rr => rr.readBinary() },
+    2: { name: 'min', read: rr => rr.readBinary() },
+    3: { name: 'null_count', read: readI64 },
+    4: { name: 'distinct_count', read: readI64 },
+    5: { name: 'max_value', read: rr => rr.readBinary() },
+    6: { name: 'min_value', read: rr => rr.readBinary() },
+  });
+}
+function readDataPageHeader(r) {
+  return readStruct(r, {
+    1: { name: 'num_values', read: readI32 },
+    2: { name: 'encoding', read: readEnum },
+    3: { name: 'definition_level_encoding', read: readEnum },
+    4: { name: 'repetition_level_encoding', read: readEnum },
+    5: { name: 'statistics', read: readStats },
+  });
+}
+function readDictionaryPageHeader(r) {
+  return readStruct(r, {
+    1: { name: 'num_values', read: readI32 },
+    2: { name: 'encoding', read: readEnum },
+    3: { name: 'is_sorted', read: (rr, type) => type === 1 ? true : type === 2 ? false : rr.readByte() !== 0 },
+  });
+}
+function readDataPageHeaderV2(r) {
+  return readStruct(r, {
+    1: { name: 'num_values', read: readI32 },
+    2: { name: 'num_nulls', read: readI32 },
+    3: { name: 'num_rows', read: readI32 },
+    4: { name: 'encoding', read: readEnum },
+    5: { name: 'definition_levels_byte_length', read: readI32 },
+    6: { name: 'repetition_levels_byte_length', read: readI32 },
+    7: { name: 'is_compressed', read: (rr, type) => type === 1 ? true : type === 2 ? false : rr.readByte() !== 0 },
+    8: { name: 'statistics', read: readStats },
+  });
+}
+function readPageHeader(r) {
+  return readStruct(r, {
+    1: { name: 'type', read: readEnum },
+    2: { name: 'uncompressed_page_size', read: readI32 },
+    3: { name: 'compressed_page_size', read: readI32 },
+    4: { name: 'data_page_header', read: readDataPageHeader },
+    6: { name: 'dictionary_page_header', read: readDictionaryPageHeader },
+    7: { name: 'data_page_header_v2', read: readDataPageHeaderV2 },
+    8: { name: 'crc', read: readI32 },
+  });
+}
+function readColumnMetaData(r) {
+  return readStruct(r, {
+    1: { name: 'type', read: readEnum },
+    2: { name: 'encodings', read: rr => readList(rr, readEnum) },
+    3: { name: 'path_in_schema', read: rr => readList(rr, readString) },
+    4: { name: 'codec', read: readEnum },
+    5: { name: 'num_values', read: readI64 },
+    6: { name: 'total_uncompressed_size', read: readI64 },
+    7: { name: 'total_compressed_size', read: readI64 },
+    8: { name: 'key_value_metadata', read: rr => readList(rr, readKeyValue) },
+    9: { name: 'data_page_offset', read: readI64 },
+    10: { name: 'index_page_offset', read: readI64 },
+    11: { name: 'dictionary_page_offset', read: readI64 },
+    12: { name: 'statistics', read: readStats },
+  });
+}
+function readColumnChunk(r) {
+  return readStruct(r, {
+    1: { name: 'file_path', read: readString },
+    2: { name: 'file_offset', read: readI64 },
+    3: { name: 'meta_data', read: readColumnMetaData },
+    4: { name: 'offset_index_offset', read: readI64 },
+    5: { name: 'offset_index_length', read: readI32 },
+    6: { name: 'column_index_offset', read: readI64 },
+    7: { name: 'column_index_length', read: readI32 },
+  });
+}
+function readRowGroup(r) {
+  return readStruct(r, {
+    1: { name: 'columns', read: rr => readList(rr, readColumnChunk) },
+    2: { name: 'total_byte_size', read: readI64 },
+    3: { name: 'num_rows', read: readI64 },
+    5: { name: 'file_offset', read: readI64 },
+    6: { name: 'total_compressed_size', read: readI64 },
+    7: { name: 'ordinal', read: readI64 },
+  });
+}
+function readFileMetaData(r) {
+  return readStruct(r, {
+    1: { name: 'version', read: readI32 },
+    2: { name: 'schema', read: rr => readList(rr, readSchemaElement) },
+    3: { name: 'num_rows', read: readI64 },
+    4: { name: 'row_groups', read: rr => readList(rr, readRowGroup) },
+    5: { name: 'key_value_metadata', read: rr => readList(rr, readKeyValue) },
+    6: { name: 'created_by', read: readString },
+  });
+}
+
+const file = fs.readFileSync('dataset.parquet');
+if (file.subarray(0, 4).toString() !== 'PAR1' || file.subarray(file.length - 4).toString() !== 'PAR1') {
+  throw new Error('not a parquet file');
+}
+const footerLen = file.readUInt32LE(file.length - 8);
+const footer = file.subarray(file.length - 8 - footerLen, file.length - 8);
+const meta = readFileMetaData(new CompactReader(footer));
+console.log(JSON.stringify({
+  version: meta.version,
+  num_rows: meta.num_rows,
+  created_by: meta.created_by,
+  schema: meta.schema,
+  row_groups: meta.row_groups.map(rg => ({
+    num_rows: rg.num_rows,
+    total_byte_size: rg.total_byte_size,
+    total_compressed_size: rg.total_compressed_size,
+    columns: rg.columns.map(c => ({
+      path: c.meta_data.path_in_schema.join('.'),
+      type: c.meta_data.type,
+      codec: c.meta_data.codec,
+      encodings: c.meta_data.encodings,
+      num_values: c.meta_data.num_values,
+      data_page_offset: c.meta_data.data_page_offset,
+      dictionary_page_offset: c.meta_data.dictionary_page_offset,
+      total_compressed_size: c.meta_data.total_compressed_size,
+      total_uncompressed_size: c.meta_data.total_uncompressed_size,
+    })),
+  })),
+}, null, 2));
+
+for (const colName of ['sex_female', 'smoking_status', 'age_years', 'pfs_months']) {
+  const col = meta.row_groups[0].columns.find(c => c.meta_data.path_in_schema.join('.') === colName);
+  console.error(`\nPAGES ${colName}`);
+  let off = col.meta_data.dictionary_page_offset ?? col.meta_data.data_page_offset;
+  let seen = 0;
+  for (let i = 0; i < 5 && off < col.meta_data.data_page_offset + col.meta_data.total_compressed_size; i++) {
+    const pr = new CompactReader(file.subarray(off));
+    const ph = readPageHeader(pr);
+    console.error(JSON.stringify({ offset: off, header_bytes: pr.pos, ph }, null, 2));
+    off += pr.pos + ph.compressed_page_size;
+    if (ph.data_page_header) seen += ph.data_page_header.num_values;
+    if (ph.data_page_header_v2) seen += ph.data_page_header_v2.num_values;
+    if (seen >= col.meta_data.num_values) break;
+  }
+}
diff --git a/C:/Users/klkehl/are_llms_biased/data/ds001/tasks/nsclc/named/probe_models.js b/C:/Users/klkehl/are_llms_biased/data/ds001/tasks/nsclc/named/probe_models.js
new file mode 100644
index 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000..c28eb539b9b9f9cc5f2db9748c408050251e44fe
--- /dev/null
+++ b/C:/Users/klkehl/are_llms_biased/data/ds001/tasks/nsclc/named/probe_models.js
@@ -0,0 +1,148 @@
+const a = require('./analyze_dataset.js');
+const { data } = a.readParquet();
+const y = data.pfs_months;
+const n = y.length;
+const arr = name => data[name];
+const z = name => a.zscore(data[name]);
+const c = name => a.center(data[name]);
+const bin = name => data[name].map(Number);
+const dummy = (name, value) => data[name].map(v => v === value ? 1 : 0);
+const scale = (values, s) => values.map(v => v * s);
+const add = (cols, name, values) => cols.concat([{ name, values }]);
+const core = [
+  { name: 'age_years', values: c('age_years') },
+  { name: 'sex_female', values: bin('sex_female') },
+  { name: 'stage_iv', values: bin('stage_iv') },
+  { name: 'has_brain_mets', values: bin('has_brain_mets') },
+  { name: 'ecog_ps', values: c('ecog_ps') },
+  { name: 'histology_squamous', values: dummy('histology', 'squamous') },
+  { name: 'smoking_current', values: dummy('smoking_status', 'current') },
+  { name: 'smoking_never', values: dummy('smoking_status', 'never') },
+];
+const severity = core.concat([
+  { name: 'albumin_g_dl', values: c('albumin_g_dl') },
+  { name: 'weight_loss_pct_6mo', values: c('weight_loss_pct_6mo') },
+  { name: 'ldh_per100', values: scale(c('ldh_u_l'), 0.01) },
+  { name: 'crp_mg_l', values: c('crp_mg_l') },
+  { name: 'nlr', values: c('nlr') },
+  { name: 'liver_mets', values: bin('liver_mets') },
+  { name: 'bone_mets', values: bin('bone_mets') },
+  { name: 'pleural_effusion', values: bin('pleural_effusion') },
+]);
+function term(model, name) {
+  return model.terms.find(t => t.name === name);
+}
+function print(name, model, terms) {
+  console.log('\n' + name);
+  for (const t of terms) {
+    const x = term(model, t);
+    console.log(`${t}\tbeta=${a.fmt(x.beta, 6)}\tse=${a.fmt(x.se, 6)}\tp=${a.ptxt(x.p)}`);
+  }
+}
+function olsPrint(name, cols, terms) {
+  const m = a.ols(y, cols);
+  print(name, m, terms);
+  return m;
+}
+// Adjusted prognostic main effects.
+olsPrint('core prognosis', severity, ['stage_iv','has_brain_mets','ecog_ps','albumin_g_dl','weight_loss_pct_6mo','ldh_per100','crp_mg_l','nlr','liver_mets','bone_mets','pleural_effusion','age_years','sex_female','histology_squamous','smoking_current','smoking_never']);
+
+const pembro = bin('treatment_pembrolizumab');
+const soto = bin('treatment_sotorasib');
+const olap = bin('treatment_olaparib');
+const osim = bin('treatment_osimertinib');
+const egfr = bin('egfr_mutation');
+const kras = bin('kras_g12c');
+const brca2 = bin('brca2_mutation');
+const stk11 = bin('stk11_mutation');
+const tmb = bin('tmb_high');
+const alk = bin('alk_fusion');
+const pdl1_10 = data.pdl1_tps.map(v => (v - a.mean(data.pdl1_tps)) / 0.1);
+
+olsPrint('pembro pdl1 interaction', severity.concat([
+  { name: 'pembrolizumab', values: pembro },
+  { name: 'pdl1_per10_centered', values: pdl1_10 },
+  { name: 'pembro_x_pdl1_per10', values: a.interactionArray(pembro, pdl1_10) },
+]), ['pembrolizumab','pdl1_per10_centered','pembro_x_pdl1_per10']);
+
+olsPrint('pembro tmb interaction', severity.concat([
+  { name: 'pembrolizumab', values: pembro },
+  { name: 'tmb_high', values: tmb },
+  { name: 'pembro_x_tmb_high', values: a.interactionArray(pembro, tmb) },
+]), ['pembrolizumab','tmb_high','pembro_x_tmb_high']);
+
+olsPrint('pembro driver resistance', severity.concat([
+  { name: 'pembrolizumab', values: pembro },
+  { name: 'egfr_mutation', values: egfr },
+  { name: 'alk_fusion', values: alk },
+  { name: 'pembro_x_egfr', values: a.interactionArray(pembro, egfr) },
+  { name: 'pembro_x_alk', values: a.interactionArray(pembro, alk) },
